The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, February 21, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Saturday, February 21, 2004				 																What to do this weekend				 																																	Attend a cultural programme to mark Martyrs Day and International Mother Language Day, organised by the Bangladesh deputy high commission and the West Bengal Federation of United Nations Association, at Sisir Manch, from 6 pm. 				 																Concert				 																																	Enjoy an evening of western classical music by La Martiniere for Boys School Orchestra at St Pauls Cathedral, 6.30 pm. Abraham Mazumder will conduct the concert.				 																Exhibitions				 																																	Drop in to CIMA Gallery for a look at Paresh Maitys water colours, 2 pm to 7 pm. Sunday closed. 				 																																	Check out Digital Art Exposition-FX 2004, organised by Arena Multimedia, at Indian Museum, noon to 8 pm.				 																Lighthouse				 																																	Dont try to catch a film at Lighthouse cinema, as police shut it down from Friday for allegedly making unauthorised changes to the premises. Hall officials have been told to submit a written application seeking permission for the changes on Monday.
